title: Nitish in touch with BJP and can return to NDA, says Manjhi
description: Former Bihar CM Jitan Ram Manjhi claimed Nitish Kumar was in touch with BJP leadership and could return to the NDA fold. Nitish objected to a proposal to make Tejashwi Yadav the CM, resulting in a change of guard in JD(U). Nitish now has assurance of support from BJP if JD(U) legislators desert the party. JD(U) accused Manjhi of spreading the rumors under BJP pressure. Nitish's possible move has generated speculation in Bihar's political circles.

title: Vikas, virasat will take India forward: PM Modi in Ayodhya
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi appeals for a blend of development and religious nationalism, linking the strength of 'vikas' and 'virasat' to take India forward. He urges people to celebrate the inauguration of the Ram Temple in Ayodhya as a national occasion and plan to visit the temple later to avoid crowding. Modi calls for a 'swachchhata abhiyan' and asks the temples to carry out a cleanliness drive. He emphasizes the need to preserve cultural heritage.

title: Pawar's dig at Centre: 'Why no full-time agriculture minister?'
Delhi cops quiz Navlakha in Mumbai for 3 hours in NewsClick case
description: Delhi Police's special investigation team interrogated activist Gautam Navlakha in Mumbai for over three hours regarding the UAPA case against web portal NewsClick. Navlakha, who is also an accused in the Bhima Koregaon-Elgar Parishad Maoist link case, has been under house arrest. The SIT questioned Navlakha about alleged funding from China and his association with the portal and its editor Prabir Purkayastha. The UAPA FIR against NewsClick also names Shanghai-based businessman Neville Roy Singham as an accused, whom Delhi Police claim infused crores to disrupt India's sovereignty and territorial integrity.

title: On SC nudge, TN CM & guv hold talks on critical issues
Sitharaman: Boost cybersecurity, check bank frauds
description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman urges public sector bank chiefs to prioritize cybersecurity and fraud prevention, including raising consumer awareness on malicious calls. Recent incidents at UCO Bank's Instant Money Payment Service (IMPS) and Bank of Baroda highlight the need for action. Sitharaman emphasizes the critical threat that frauds pose to customers and banks, leading to losses and eroding public trust. Banks must remain vigilant in fraud prevention, educate customers on safe banking, and identify fraudulent accounts.

title: India records 7 Covid deaths, 743 new cases
Govt issues 'draft' for ease of rail travel for divyangs
description: The Centre has issued a draft rule to ensure accessibility for people with disabilities at railway stations and trains. The proposed rules aim to create a user-friendly environment and seek feedback from stakeholders and the public. The guidelines emphasize dedicated website features, a mobile app, and a one-click template for people with disabilities. Credible announcements & accessible entry and exit points are also proposed. The guidelines aim to enhance overall accessibility and provide a more inclusive experience.

title: Ahead of polls, BJP candidate takes oath in Raj
description: Rajasthan CM Bhajanlal Sharma formed his cabinet with 22 ministers taking the oath of office at Raj Bhavan in Jaipur. The notable inclusions are Sawai Madhopur MLA Kirori Lal Meena, Jhotwara MLA Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore, and Surendra Pal Singh TT, the BJP candidate for Karanpur assembly seat. There is criticism from Congress for violating the model code of conduct. The state's council of ministers now has 25 members and for the first time, it doesn't include any Muslim members

title: Like Ram Lalla, 4cr people have got own homes: PM in Ayodhya
description: Modi emphasizes development and devotion can coexist, highlighting India's progress in digital technology and preservation of pilgrimage sites. Ram Lalla now has a permanent temple, and 4 crore people have received permanent houses under PM Awas Yojana. Modi links the consecration ceremony with a cleanliness drive and urges temples to participate. He urges Ayodhya to prepare for a large influx of tourists and advises people to plan visits after January 22 for security reasons. Modi asserts the importance of preserving cultural heritage for a progressing country and mentions various development projects across India.

title: ‘Pregnant Job Agency’ busted in Bihar, 8 arrested
description: Bihar gang runs 'All India Pregnant Job Agency' in Nawada district, luring people with the promise of high returns. Eight members of the gang were arrested, but the kingpin escaped. Victims were asked to pay a registration fee and a security deposit between Rs 5,000 to Rs 20,000 to impregnate selected women. Successful men were promised a prize money of Rs 13 lakh, while unsuccessful ones were assured a consolation prize of Rs 5 lakh.

title: 10 int'l airlines under DGGI scanner over tax evasion
description: The Directorate General of GST Intelligence (DGGI) has questioned executives from at least 10 leading foreign airlines in an ongoing investigation related to alleged tax evasion. Finance managers of British Airways, Etihad, Thai Airways, and Qatar Airways have recorded their statements. Lufthansa, Emirates, Oman Airlines, and Singapore Airlines have not yet appeared for questioning. DGGI has asked the airlines to produce documents related to their India-related expenditure and pay tax for services rendered under the new GST regime.

title: Local terror recruitment down 80% in 2023: JK DGP
description: Jammu and Kashmir witnessed an 80% decline in local terror recruitment in 2023, with foreigners taking the lead, according to DGP RR Swain. Only 22 recruitments occurred in 2023, and the J&K Police aims to curtail recruitment and violence. The collaborative efforts of the police and other security forces resulted in the neutralization of 113 terrorists, leaving 31 local operatives active. Additionally, two separatist organisations, the DFP and the Muslim League were banned under UAPA.

title: Earthquake shakes part of Indonesia's Papua region
description: A powerful earthquake shook Papua, Indonesia's easternmost region, causing no serious damage. The magnitude 6.5 quake occurred in Abepura, a subdistrict in Jayapura, the capital of Papua province. It was a shallow earthquake with a depth of 10 kilometers. The region is prone to earthquakes due to its location on the "Ring of Fire". In February, another earthquake in the province resulted in the collapse of a floating restaurant, causing four deaths. Indonesia has a history of earthquakes and volcanic eruptions, with past disasters claiming many lives.

title: Seat sharing talks in MVA will proceed smoothly: Uddhav
Ayodhya 2.0: Temple town gets new look ahead of 'historic' Ram temple consecration ceremony
description: A swanky new railway station, a state-of-the-art airport and streets bedecked with flowers, Ayodhya has undergone a stunning makeover just three weeks ahead of the Ram mandir consecration ceremony.On Saturday, after inaugurating a slew of projects, PM Modi gave a clarion call to the entire nation to prepare for the historic moment of the "pran pratishtha" on January 22.“The whole world is waiting for the historic moment of the 'pran pratishtha' ceremony in Ayodhya on January 22,” PM Modi said at a mega rally in Ayodhya.

title: 2nd Women's ODI: India fall short as Australia seal series
description: Richa Ghosh's career-best 96 and Deepti Sharma's 5/38 went in vain as Australia Women clinched a thrilling three-run win to take an unassailable 2-0 lead against India in their three-match ODI series in Mumbai on Saturday.

title: Pakhawaj maestro Pandit Bhavani passes away due to cardiac arrest
description: Pandit Bhawani Shankar was a renowned 'pakhawaj' player and one of the best we saw in the field of Indian classical music. He passed away on Saturday due to cardiac arrest...

title: Biden raises alarm on US being pulled into clash with Russia
'Devil comet', bigger than Mt Everest, racing towards Earth
Nikki Haley vows to pardon Trump if elected US president
Why job offers have declined for Harvard MBA grads
Manipur: Unidentified gunmen target police commandos
Vinesh Phogat returns Khel Ratna and Arjuna Awards
description: Multiple World Championship medallist Vinesh Phogat on Saturday returned her Khel Ratna and Arjuna Award, keeping the two awards lying in the middle of national capital's Kartavya Path after Delhi Police stopped her from reaching the prime minister's office.

title: 2nd Test: Rohit focuses on Mukesh during net session
description: It was an optional session at the Supersport Park but for India skipper Rohit Sharma, skipping the nets wasn't an option. Outfoxed by South African pace spearhead Kagiso Rabada in both innings of the opening Test, Rohit was present as skipper and batter in equal measure during a two-hour session.

title: Pak election body rejects Imran Khan's nomination for 2024 polls
'An innings defeat is quite...': Former opener slams India batters
description: A below-par bowling performance was followed shock batting collapse in the second innings as India succumbed to an embarrassing defeat in the Test series opener against South Africa in Centurion. India batted just over 100 overs in both innings combined as a fiery Proteas wrapped up the Boxing Day Test inside three days to hand India one of their worst defeats in the Rainbow Nation.

title: Flyers' Ramayan-inspired name for inaugural Ayodhya flight
description: Passengers on IndiGo's first commercial flight to Ayodhya described it as a pilgrimage on Pushpak vimaan. The flight operated from Maharishi Valmiki International Airport Ayodhya Dham, soon after Prime Minister Modi inaugurated it. People flocked to Ayodhya to visit the Ram Lalla temple. Some passengers carried holy soil and jal from Hanumanji's birthplace, Kishkindha Parvat. The flight was a divine blessing for them. The atmosphere at the airport was electric, with chanting of Ram dhun and Hanuman Chalisa.

title: Rajasthan cabinet expansion: 22 MLAs take oath as ministers
World waiting for Ram temple consecration: PM
Watch: Why Gavaskar refused to accept Pathan's apology
description: Former India all-rounder Irfan Pathan impressed legendary Sunil Gavaskar with his cricket acumen while analysing KL Rahul's magnificent knock of 101 in the first innings of the first Test against South Africa. Pathan commended Rahul's performance, emphasizing his technique and batting style. Upon realising that his analysis is getting longer, Pathan extended an apology saying 'Sir sorry' to the living legend Gavaskar.

title: Watch: Why Gavaskar refuses to accept Pathan's apology

title: In Ayodhya, PM Modi stops for tea at Ujjwala beneficiary's house
Indian-origin couple, daughter found dead in Massachusetts
description: An Indian-origin couple and their teenage daughter were found dead in a $5 million Dover mansion in Massachusetts in a suspected domestic violence incident. The bodies of Rakesh Kamal (57), his wife, Teena (54), and their 18-year-old daughter, Ariana, were discovered. The couple had previously run a now-defunct education systems company called EduNova. The district attorney described the incident as a "terrible tragedy" and stated that a gun was found near the husband's body. The investigation is ongoing and there is no indication of outside involvement.

title: Bajrang urges Sports Ministry to restart wrestling activities
description: Olympic medallist Bajrang Punia on Saturday urged the Sports Ministry to restart the wrestling activities in the country with just seven months remaining for next year's Paris Games, and said no one seemed to have taken the preparations for the quadrennial showpiece seriously.

title: 'Warner is not a selector': Aussie head coach
description: David Warner might have endorsed Marcus Harris as his successor for opening slot in Tests, but Australia head coach Andrew McDonald said they are considering a lot more options and Cameron Green is also in contention. Warner will retire from Test cricket after the third match against Pakistan at Sydney beginning on January 3.

title: Amritsar Delhi Vande Bharat: Golden Temple town to Delhi in 6hrs
description: Amritsar to Delhi Vande Bharat Express: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will on December 30, 2023 flag off the new Amritsar to Delhi Junction Vande Bharat Express train.

title: Follow these five tips to extend the battery life of your iPhone
description: This article discusses tips to optimize battery life on iPhones. Adjust screen brightness and timeout settings to conserve power. Disable background app refresh for apps that don't need constant updates. Customize location access for apps to reduce battery drain. Use Wi-Fi instead of cellular data whenever possible. Activate Low Power Mode to extend battery life.

title: Amrit Bharat Express Darbhanga-Ayodhya-Anand Vihar: Check schedule, ticket price
description: Amrit Bharat Express Darbhanga-Ayodhya-Anand Vihar Delhi: PM Narendra Modi will flag off the all new Amrit Bharat Express train between Darbhanga and Anand Vihar Terminal Delhi via Ayodhya today.

title: Xiaomi's first electric car claims to have 'better' tech than Tesla
description: Xiaomi enters electric vehicle market with SU7 Max sedan, boasting impressive features and specifications. The car is powered by Xiaomi's HyperEngine electric motors, offering faster acceleration than Tesla's Model S. It has a long driving range of up to 800km on a single charge. The SU7 Max is built on Xiaomi's Modena Architecture, surpassing Tesla's vehicles in terms of chassis strength. It features Xiaomi's HyperOS in-car entertainment system and optional Xiaomi Pad tablets for rear-seat entertainment. The car is equipped with Xiaomi's Pilot autonomous driving platform and supports integration with third-party smart car features. The SU7 Max is expected to be launched in China in 2024.

title: 'There is a question mark': Former India batter on Gill
description: Cricket commentator and former India player Aakash Chopra has said Shubman Gill has "a slight technical deficiency in his batting" and while this approach may suit flat pitches and white ball cricket, "it does not work in Test cricket". Gill, 24, has played 19 Test matches for the nation since making his debut in 2020 against Australia in Melbourne. He has scored 994 runs in 35 innings at an average of 31.06. However, when one looks in depth, his statistics suggest that he has struggled against the red-ball giants like New Zealand, England and now South Africa.

title: Vande Bharat Jalna to Mumbai: Check schedule, ticket price
description: Train number 20705 Jalna-CSMT Vande Bharat Express will depart from Jalna at 5:05 AM to reach CSMT at 11:55 AM taking 6 hours and 50 minutes. En route the train will stop at Aurangabad, Manmad Junction, Nasik Road, Kalyan Junction, Thane, Dadar stations.

title: PM to flag off 2 new Amrit Bharat, 6 Vande Bharat Express trains
description: Vande Bharat, Amrit Bharat Express flag off: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will be flagging off a total of eight new trains on December 30, 2023. These include two new Amrit Bharat Express trains and six new Vande Bharat Express train services.

title: Headmistress suspended for kissing student during school excursion
Pre-wedding shoot over Ganga goes awry in Uttarakhand
Govt declares Lakhbir Singh Landa as ‘terrorist’
Stabbed 50 times: Insta date gone wrong leads to Delhi murder
description: Arman Khan, an 18-year-old, is now in judicial custody as the prime suspect in a murder case in Bhagirathi Vihar, Delhi. Arman had met a woman on Instagram and believed they were in love. However, an argument ensued when he discovered that she preferred another man named Mahir. In a plot to get revenge, Arman lured Mahir to a meeting spot under the guise of returning the woman's phone and proceeded to stab him to death. Arman, along with two friends, has been arrested and is awaiting trial.

title: Why India seem lost in South Africa
description: Broadcasters coined enticing taglines such as the 'Final Frontier' to boost India's quest for their inaugural Test series victory in South Africa. However, the reality diverged significantly as India experienced a feeble surrender in the Centurion Test. Yet, South Africa is not the sole destination where India has encountered challenges while playing abroad. For the record, of the last 20 Tests that India have played in New Zealand, they have won only one, in Hamilton in 2009.

title: Google agrees to settle $5 billion lawsuit over 'incognito' mode
World population to hit 8 billion on January 1
RIL will be among world's top 10 biz groups: Ambani
description: Mukesh Ambani, chairman and MD of Reliance Industries, aims to place his conglomerate among the world's top 10 business groups. Ambani emphasized the importance of taking bold and courageous steps, learning from past errors, and avoiding complacency. He highlighted Reliance's track record of disrupting markets through innovation and reinvention. The conglomerate has transformed from a traditional energy and materials enterprise to a technology player with its telecom and digital services. Ambani urged employees to embrace an ownership mindset.

title: Gunmen kill 6 people in northern Mexico border state
How watermelon has become a symbol of Palestinian solidarity
description: Watermelons are being used as a symbol of solidarity with Palestinians in the Israel-Hamas war. The fruit is painted on cardboard at protests and appears on social media next to the Palestinian flag. It represents identity and resistance for Palestinians. The watermelon emoji is part of the symbols used in social media debates about the war. It has roots in Israel's suppression of the Palestinian flag and its use dates back to the 1967-1993 ban. Watermelon imagery has attracted both support and scrutiny during the conflict.

title: At 7.8%, core sector growth slows to 6-month low in November
Cognizant gets High Court relief in tax case
5 skeletons found in K'taka house, family was last seen in '19
description: Police in Chitradurga discovered the skeletal remains of five family members, including Jagannath Reddy, Prema, Triveni, Krishna, and Narendra. The family members were last seen in 2019 and their residence has remained locked since then. The bodies were found in two separate rooms, with signs of multiple break-ins. The exact cause of death is unknown and is being investigated. The home minister has called for an identification of the victims and an inquiry into how their absence went unnoticed.
